# Design System

Follow the visual identity documented in:

- docs/02-design-system.md

Do not invent a different visual style.

---

# Design Philosophy

Every interface should communicate:

- Quiet luxury
- Timeless elegance
- Warmth
- Editorial minimalism
- Romance
- Spaciousness

Every design decision should support these principles.

---

# Layout

Prefer:

- Large whitespace
- Clear visual hierarchy
- Balanced composition
- Comfortable reading width
- Generous vertical spacing

Avoid:

- Crowded layouts
- Small touch targets
- Unnecessary decorative elements

---

# Typography

Respect the project's typography system.

Use typography to establish hierarchy rather than changing colors or adding excessive decoration.

Avoid:

- Too many font sizes
- Inconsistent font weights
- Decorative fonts outside their intended purpose

---

# Colors

Only use colors defined in the Design System.

Do not introduce random colors.

Do not use default Tailwind colors unless they are mapped to project design tokens.

---

# Components

Components should feel:

- Elegant
- Spacious
- Consistent
- Minimal

Avoid overly busy UI.

Reuse existing components whenever possible.

---

# Buttons

Buttons should have:

- Clear hierarchy
- Consistent sizing
- Accessible contrast
- Comfortable padding

Primary actions should always be visually obvious.

---

# Cards

Cards should emphasize content rather than decoration.

Prefer:

- Soft borders
- Rounded corners
- Generous padding
- Minimal shadow

Avoid heavy borders and exaggerated elevation.

---

# Icons

Use simple outline icons.

Icons should support content rather than become decorative elements.

Keep icon sizing consistent throughout the project.

---

# Motion

Animations should feel:

- Calm
- Smooth
- Intentional
- Premium

Prefer:

- Fade
- Gentle slide
- Soft scale

Avoid:

- Bounce
- Spin
- Flash
- Elastic effects
- Distracting motion

Motion should enhance the experience, not compete with it.

---

# Images

Images should appear:

- Bright
- Natural
- Authentic
- Editorial

Prefer large, immersive imagery.

Always preserve image quality.

Use the Next.js Image component where appropriate.

---

# Responsive Design

Design mobile-first.

Layouts should adapt gracefully across:

- Mobile
- Tablet
- Desktop

Never sacrifice usability for aesthetics.

---

# Consistency

Maintain consistency across:

- Colors
- Typography
- Spacing
- Border radius
- Iconography
- Motion
- Component behavior

Do not introduce one-off styles.

---

# User Experience

Every screen should answer:

"What is the next action for the user?"

Guide users naturally through the wedding story.

Avoid unnecessary friction.

---

# Final Check

Before completing UI work, verify:

- Matches the documented Design System
- Feels cohesive with the rest of the application
- Uses consistent spacing
- Uses consistent typography
- Uses approved colors
- Uses calm, refined motion
- Delivers a premium experience